Title: qmtsvr:An API for fitting (Quasi)Multi-task support vector regression using the kernlab library
Package: qmtsvr
Imports: kernlab, foreach, doParallel
Type: Package
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Anderson Alves
Maintainer: Anderson A.C. Alves <alves.zootecnista@gmail.com>
Description: This package uses data-augmentation for exploring the complementary information of correlated traits for genome-wide prediction of a primary trait of interest using the Support Vector Regression.
    The main functionalities are:  
    a) qmtsvr.dist: A function for computing Weighted Euclidean Distance Matrix (WEDM) based on an n x p numeric matrix (e.g. Matrix of SNPs).
    b) qmtsvr.GA: Metaheuristic search of the QMTSVR hyperparameters using a Genetic Algorithm.
    c) qmtsvr.fit: Fits a QMTSVR model given the user-defined hyperparameters.
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
